Traffic Signs in the city of Antwerp

Oliver Hofkens

7/4/2017

Summary

The following is a map of 20k traffic signs in the city of Antwerp (http://opendata.antwerpen.be/datasets/verkeersborden). They are clustered based on location (try zooming in and out!), and will show the fabrication date + the text of the sign when clicked (if any).

data = read.csv("http://datasets.antwerpen.be/v4/gis/verkeersbordpt.csv", sep=";")
library("leaflet")

map <- leaflet() %>%
    addTiles() %>%
    addMarkers(data$point_lng, data$point_lat, group=data$beeldvlak ,clusterOptions=markerClusterOptions(), popup=paste(data$fabdatum, data$opschrift, sep="<br>"))
map
